---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Blog" 
  description="Expert insights on Japanese landscaping, Ueki techniques, Bonsai care, and garden design philosophy."
>
  <!-- Blog -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Blog</h1>
      
      <div class="blog-list">
        <!-- Blog Post 1 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1585320806297-9794b3e4eeae?w=800&q=80" alt="Pruning Japanese garden tree" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Techniques</span>
            <h2>Essential Pruning Techniques for Japanese Garden Trees</h2>
            <p>Learn the fundamental Niwaki pruning techniques that have shaped Japanese gardens for centuries, from branch selection to seasonal timing.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Blog Post 2 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516253593875-bd7ba052fbc5?w=800&q=80" alt="Bonsai tree" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Bonsai Basics</span>
            <h2>Choosing Your First Bonsai: A Beginner's Guide</h2>
            <p>Starting your Bonsai journey? Discover which species are best for beginners and what to look for when selecting your first tree.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Blog Post 3 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1604608672516-f1b6123627b7?w=800&q=80" alt="Japanese maple" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Plant Care</span>
            <h2>Seasonal Care Guide: Japanese Maples in Your Garden</h2>
            <p>Japanese maples are stunning focal points in any garden. Learn how to care for them through each season for optimal health and color.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Blog Post 4 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519552928909-5ca50ae0d54d?w=800&q=80" alt="Japanese garden design" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Design Philosophy</span>
            <h2>Five Principles of Japanese Garden Design</h2>
            <p>Understanding the philosophical foundations of Japanese garden design: asymmetry, simplicity, naturalness, subtlety, and stillness.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Blog Post 5 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509937528035-ad76254b0356?w=800&q=80" alt="Bonsai repotting" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Bonsai Techniques</span>
            <h2>Bonsai Repotting: When, Why, and How</h2>
            <p>Repotting is crucial for Bonsai health. Learn to recognize when your tree needs repotting and master the step-by-step process.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        
        <!-- Blog Post 6 -->
        <article class="blog-post">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1560961911-ba7ef651a56c?w=800&q=80" alt="Wabi-sabi aesthetic" />
          <div class="post-content">
            <span class="category">Design Philosophy</span>
            <h2>Creating Wabi-Sabi Aesthetic in Small Spaces</h2>
            <p>Embrace the beauty of imperfection and impermanence. Learn how to bring Wabi-Sabi principles to your compact garden or patio.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .blog-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  }
  
  .blog-post {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    align-items: start;
  }
  
  .blog-post img {
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  
  .category {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--color-background);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .post-content h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .post-content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .blog-post {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
